title: For Sale:  Brazilian Mauser 98 Short
postcontent: This is a Brazilian Mauser 98 Short made by DWM in Berlin. This carbine version is somewhat uncommon, especially the unmodified originals. The 98 action is world–renowned and arguable the best bolt action ever designed. Most modern bolt actions are either copies or direct descendants of this legendary system. Features of the design include three bolt locking lugs for added safety and gas vents to vent dangerous hot gas away from shooters eyes in case of malfunction. The quality and work that went into these rifles really gives a peak into the old-world craftmanship that we dont see anymore.Pros:Shoots great and reliablyAction is still in the white and very smooth to operateBore is clean although the pictures maybe fuzzy (surprisingly difficult to photograph a rifle barrel clearly).Cons:Has acquired a petina with age (ripe for a restoration, would be a beautiful piece with a bit of TLC)Top handguard is crackedLight pitting around the action along where the woods meets the steelPriced to sell. title: For Sale:  9 MM Model 92 Taurus (Beretta Mfg License)
postcontent:
This 9 MM caliber Taurus Model 92 is made on the license of the famous Beretta 92 series. The open top slide virtually eliminates jamming and stove piping and allows the user to load and chamber one cartridge at a time should the magazine be lost or damaged.
FEATURES: Safeties:  ambidextrous safety on both sides of frame. 
 
Nicely visible, high profile white 3 dot sight system.
Rear sights are fully adjustable for windage and elevation. Loaded chamber indicator along side barrel.
Single and double action. Single action has a nice clean break -- it’s short, light (about five pounds) and crisp!
Real hammer fired – this is the classic hammer you can pull back with your thumb and actually feel and see firing the gun, a feature favored by many shooters as a more authentic shooting experience.
Breech-locking mechanism uses a Walther-style tilting locking block.
Construction: Steel barrel and slide.  Sturdy metal alloy frame.
5 inch barrel and military/ergonomic frame achieves legendary pointability and accuracy.
Recoil is very manageable. Strong, planted grip with checkered wood grips means that the recoil does not snap or kick  --  more of a "push" and really cushions the recoil.  Even shooters accustomed to a lighter round will be able to handle it very easily.
Full Pachmayr Signatur Grips have full checkering all around (360 degrees) for a secure grip.
Double stack, high capacity magazine.
Field stripping is a snap, using Beretta’s sure-footed, quick lever takedown that easily removes the slide from the frame. From there, the recoil spring, guide tube and barrel are easily removed.
Unbeatable Taurus lifetime warranty (transferrable to all subsequent owners).
**  The features, fit and finish of its more expensive cousins that it easily rivals. Note the absence of machine marks, a characteristic of higher end firearms.
Carry options:  Drop the hammer by thumbing the safety lever all the way down and carry it chambered, hammer down, off safe for a first double action shot.  You can also keep the safety on, then thumb it off with and have a first double action shot.  If you are a 1911 fan, then you can also carry cocked and locked which is the hammer cocked, safety on with a first shot being single action.
Includes high capacity magazine.
